From: AGX team
Subject: [PATCH] zero JBD descriptor/commit/revoke blocks before partial-write

Every transactional update during populate writes:

  - A descriptor block (`jbd_journal_prepare`) with a header
    + a tag table that may not fill the whole block.
  - A commit block (`jbd_trans_write_commit_block`) with a
    ~64-byte jbd_commit_header followed by ~4 KiB of unused
    space.
  - A revoke block (`jbd_journal_prepare_revoke`) with a
    header + a record area that may not fill the block.

All three call `jbd_block_get_noread`, which hands back
whatever was in the buffer cache, then overwrite only the
structured prefix.  The tail bytes go to disk as stale heap.

Result: identical mkfs + populate runs produce disk.ext4
images that diverge in journal blocks 1..N (the heap state
varies run to run), AND a small data-leak from agxd's
process memory into the persistent filesystem on every
transaction.

Fix: memset the full block to zero immediately after the
noread, before any structured writes.
--- a/src/ext4_journal.c
+++ b/src/ext4_journal.c
@@ -1779,6 +1779,11 @@ static int jbd_trans_write_commit_block(struct jbd_trans *trans)
 	rc = jbd_block_get_noread(journal->jbd_fs, &block, commit_iblock);
 	if (rc != EOK)
 		return rc;
+	/* AGX: zero the whole block before stamping the commit
+	 * header — the noread buffer carries uninitialised heap
+	 * past the ~64 byte header, which would otherwise leak
+	 * to disk. */
+	memset(block.data, 0, journal->block_size);

 	header = (struct jbd_commit_header *)block.data;
 	jbd_set32(&header->header, magic, JBD_MAGIC_NUMBER);
@@ -1900,6 +1905,8 @@ static int jbd_journal_prepare(struct jbd_journal *journal,
 			rc = jbd_block_get_noread(journal->jbd_fs, &desc_block, desc_iblock);
 			if (rc != EOK)
 				break;
+			/* AGX: zero the whole desc block (tag table tail). */
+			memset(desc_block.data, 0, journal->block_size);

 			bhdr = (struct jbd_bhdr *)desc_block.data;
 			jbd_set32(bhdr, magic, JBD_MAGIC_NUMBER);
@@ -2020,6 +2027,8 @@ static int jbd_journal_prepare_revoke(struct jbd_journal *journal,
 			rc = jbd_block_get_noread(journal->jbd_fs, &desc_block,
 						  desc_iblock);
 			if (rc != EOK)
 				break;
+			/* AGX: zero the whole revoke block (record-area tail). */
+			memset(desc_block.data, 0, journal->block_size);

 			bhdr = (struct jbd_bhdr *)desc_block.data;
 			jbd_set32(bhdr, magic, JBD_MAGIC_NUMBER);
